"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150116","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-23","<p>Under the framework established by the Legal Services Act 2007, the legal profession in England and Wales, and the bodies that regulate it, are independent from government. It is the responsibility of the Legal Services Board, as oversight regulator, to ensure that the approved regulators are complying with the regulatory objectives set out in the 2007 Act.</p>","Croydon South","Chris Philp","958 ; 959 ; 960 ; 961","2019-10-23T16:57:47.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150116/answer","Biography information for Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150116/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150116/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-16","Solicitors Regulation Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the Solicitors Regulation Authority has a code of conduct for its staff working in the (a) the Investigation and Supervision Unit, (b) Forensic Investigation Unit and (c) Legal and Enforcement Unit.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","957"
