"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149236","Home Office","false","2019-11-05","<p>There has been significant outreach and communication activities to reach those most likely to have been affected by the issues around Windrush.</p><p>To reach international audiences, a High Commissioners event was hosted by the former Immigration Minister to further raise awareness, and working with the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, a briefing was provided to embassies to inform local conversations. Plans are in development for additional activity overseas.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy",,"2019-11-05T16:58:10.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149236/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149236/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149236/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-10-15","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she has taken to promote the (a) Windrush Helpline and (b) Windrush Compensation Scheme to individuals in (i) India, (ii) Pakistan, (iii) Bangladesh, (iv) Kenya, (v) Singapore, (vi) Malta, (vii) South Africa, (viii) Canada and (ix) Nigeria; and how much has been spent in doing so.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149237","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-10-21","<p>Terms of Reference for the Serious Case Panel have not yet been finalised. When they are a copy will be placed in the House of Commons library.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2019-10-21T16:04:57.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149237/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149237/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149237/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-10-15","Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when she will publish the terms of reference of her Department's new Serious Case Panel.","false","Biography information for Marsha De Cordova","Battersea","Marsha De Cordova","655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149238","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-10-21","<p><strong>T</strong>he Department is currently developing Panel membership and intends to work with stakeholders as the Panel is agreed.</p><p />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2019-10-21T16:09:31.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149238/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149238/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149238/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-10-15","Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether (a) disabled people and (b) representatives from disabled people's organisations will sit on her Department's new independent Serious Case panel.","false","Biography information for Marsha De Cordova","Battersea","Marsha De Cordova","656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149239","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-10-21","<p>A combination of independent experts and Directors from the Department will sit on the new Serious Case Panel. To get the balance right the Department will work with stakeholders as the Panel is developed.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2019-10-21T16:22:29.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149239/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149239/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149239/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-10-15","Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, who will sit on her Department's new independent Serious Case panel.","false","Biography information for Marsha De Cordova","Battersea","Marsha De Cordova","657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149240","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-21","<p>No comparative assessment has been made of the merits of splitting Norfolk and Suffolk Foundation Trust into separate trusts and retaining it as a single trust.</p><p><br> Norfolk and Suffolk Foundation Trust is committed to delivering improved services for its patients in Norfolk and Suffolk in line with the agreed local mental health strategies for children, adults and older people in Norfolk and Suffolk. It is working collaboratively with its National Health Service and local authority partners to strengthen the local accountability of services and ensure that they are developed in a more integrated way with other local providers, for the benefit of patients in both Norfolk and Suffolk.</p><p> </p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-10-21T13:12:13.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149240/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149240/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149240/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-15","Norfolk and Suffolk NHS Foundation Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what comparative assessment his Department has made of the merits of (a) splitting Norfolk & Suffolk Foundation Trust into separate trusts and (b) retaining that Trust as a single trust.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149241","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-21","<p>Ministers and officials meet regularly with a range of bus operators to discuss a variety of issues. A record of ministerial meetings is available at: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/dataset/789fd6df-87a9-4144-bc59-62b0b84e59f0/department-for-transport-ministerial-and-special-adviser-meetings-with-external-organisations-including-meetings-with-newspaper-and-other-media-proprietors-editors-and-senior-executives" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/dataset/789fd6df-87a9-4144-bc59-62b0b84e59f0/department-for-transport-ministerial-and-special-adviser-meetings-with-external-organisations-including-meetings-with-newspaper-and-other-media-proprietors-editors-and-senior-executives</a></p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2019-10-21T15:18:59.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149241/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149241/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149241/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-15","First Group: Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with First Group UK on (a) the provision of bus transport in the UK and (b) their plans for the divestment of their UK bus division.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149242","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Bus Services Act 2017 provides mayoral combined authorities with automatic access to franchising powers.</p><p> </p><p>Other local authorities may franchise bus services with the consent of the Secretary of State. Guidance on what the Secretary of State will consider in deciding whether to franchise is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/831690/bus-services-act-2017-franchising-scheme-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/831690/bus-services-act-2017-franchising-scheme-guidance.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>We have no plans to change these arrangements at present.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2019-10-23T10:20:08.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149242/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149242/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149242/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-15","Bus Services: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has plans to extend the provisions of the Bus Services Act 2017 in respect of franchising bus services to local transport authorities other than Combined Authorities.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149243","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-21","<p>We do not hold the number of referrals for fire related events in prison centrally and this information could only be obtained at disproportionate costs</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-10-21T14:58:03.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149243/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149243/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149243/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-15","Prisons: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the Answer of 8 October 2019 to Question 293577 on Prisons: Fires, how many CPS referrals for prosecution in 2018 involved fire events in prisons.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149244","Home Office","false","2019-11-05","<p>The report relates to applications from failed asylum seekers for support under section 4 of the Immigration and Asylum Act 1999. We aim to decide most of these applications within 5 working days, or 2 days of the Home Office reviewing the application if the person is vulnerable, but some take longer because of the need to make further enquiries to establish that the person is eligible to receive the support.</p><p>The issue has been discussed with the authors of the report and a process through which voluntary sector organisations can escalate concerns about delays in individual cases has been agreed.</p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-11-05T11:11:20.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149244/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149244/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149244/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-10-15","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the report entitled, Missing the safety net, published by Refugee Action, what processes her Department has in place to escalate support for applications that have been delayed beyond her Department's guidelines on the processing of applications; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Sir George Howarth","425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149245","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-21","<p>There is no statutory requirement for a military or legal review of the decision to maintain the United Kingdom's nuclear deterrent.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan",,"2019-10-21T10:58:30.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149245/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149245/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149245/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-15","Trident","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether there is a statutory requirement for a (a) military and (b) legal review of the Trident Replacement Decision.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149246","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>Access (the Foundation for Social Investment) has launched its 'Local Access' programme together with Big Society Capital. This programme will provide a blend of grant and repayable investment worth at least £33m across five places in England. This includes £15 million of repayable social investment from Big Society Capital (the UK’s social investment wholesaler set up with dormant account money), £8 million of funding from Access’s endowment for enterprise development, and £10million of recently released dormant accounts money for place-based investment. The first round of funding will be released to the chosen five places in early 2020. The objective of the programme is to support the growth of the social economy in local places and in doing so help reduce poverty and inequality.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:55:53.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149246/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149246/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149246/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 14 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken to work with partners to develop new models of community funding.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149247","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Civil Society Strategy sets out our vision for government’s work with and for civil society over the next 10 years and beyond. The Strategy recognises the importance of government working together with the sector to maintain its health, independence and influence. We are exploring options for renewing the government’s commitment to the principles of the Compact.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:54:18.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149247/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149247/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149247/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 14 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what plans her Department has to renew its commitment to the Compact.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149248","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Civil Society Strategy sets out our vision for the government’s work with and for civil society over the next 10 years and beyond. The Strategy recognised the need for the government to work with civil society, the Electoral Commission, and the Charity Commission to develop non-legislative steps to increase the confidence in civil society to speak out.</p><p> </p><p>In September, the Electoral Commission released new guidance to clarify rules on charity campaigning spending in the lead up to unscheduled general elections so they could campaign with confidence all year round.</p><p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission developed this guidance following engagement with charities, the Charity Commission and government. The new guidance has been welcomed by charities.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:54:38.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149248/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149248/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149248/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 14 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken to work with (a) civil society, (b) the Electoral Commission and (c) the charity commission to explore what non-legislative steps could strengthen civil society’s confidence in speaking out.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149249","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Civil Society Strategy sets out our vision for government’s work with and for civil society over the next 10 years and beyond. The Strategy recognised the need to work with civil society and across government to establish principles of effective involvement in the policy-making process. The details of this cross-government group will be set out in due course.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:55:05.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149249/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149249/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149249/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 15 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken towards convening a cross-government group to work with civil society to establish the principles of effective involvement in the policy-making process.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149250","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Civil Society Strategy sets out our vision for government’s work with and for civil society over the next 10 years and beyond. The Strategy recognised the demand from the social enterprise sector for a simpler relationship with the government and committed to establishing a regular forum for social enterprises to coordinate relations with government. The details of the forum will be set out in due course.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:55:31.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149250/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149250/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149250/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 15 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken to establish a regular forum for social enterprises to co-ordinate relations with Government.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149251","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>By the end of March 2019, the Revitalising Trusts Programme, delivered in conjunction with the Charity Commission and UKCF, had released over £11 million worth of funds from dormant charitable trusts, reinvesting this in local communities. This funding will support local good causes across the country.</p><p> </p><p>The programme is on track and we expect to reach our target of at least £20 million by the end of March 2020.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:56:12.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149251/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149251/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149251/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 15 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what progress her Department has made on working with (a) the Charity Commission and (b) UK Community Foundations to release at least £20 million from inactive charitable trusts to help community organisations.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149252","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>Since the publication of the Civil Society Strategy, DCMS has funded the Centre for Acceleration of Social Technology (CAST), Social Tech Trust, and Nesta Challenges, among other partners, to strengthen the digital resilience of the social sector. Activities range from establishing investment funds through to launching challenge prizes. We have also built the skills and capability of charity leaders by funding 13 training and support providers, through the £1 million Digital Leadership Fund.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:58:55.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149252/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149252/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149252/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 15 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what progress her Department has made on working with partners to explore how best to use digital technology to build a stronger and more effective social sector.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149253","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>We will publish a short public update on government’s approach to Responsible Business in the coming months, including an update on the Inclusive Economy Partnership.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:56:30.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149253/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149253/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149253/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 15 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, when her Department plans to provide an update on its approach to support for responsible business.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149254","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Department, together with BEIS, has consulted with key stakeholders from business and civil society as a first phase of establishing the Responsible Business Leadership Group. We have also held early conversations with potential candidates for chairs, and are considering membership composition. We are also carefully considering the relationship of the group to other business councils, to ensure that the group is complementary to these. We are also conducting research as input to the group on what specific questions it should seek to answer; and have initiated research into potential engagement with academic institutions. The Secretary of State will be making an announcement on the chairs once they are confirmed.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:59:34.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149254/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149254/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149254/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 15 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken towards establishing a Responsible Business Leadership Group.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149255","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Civil Society Strategy is a forward-looking long-term strategy. We continue to promote community engagement in commissioning to stakeholders at relevant meetings and events including the Commissioning Academy for public sector decision makers across the country. We have held discussions with organisations involved in Citizen Commissioners schemes to understand success factors and options for the future.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:56:55.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149255/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149255/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149255/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 16 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken to support the spread of Citizen Commissioners.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149256","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Government currently runs a support programme for public service mutuals. Following a series of engagement events, the then Minister for Civil Society launched a public consultation on the future definition of public service mutuals on 19th July 2019. The consultation, which closed on 18th October 2019, included proposals to widen the current definition to include organisations that don’t originate in the public sector and to strengthen and clarify requirements around employee influence, independence, and the distribution of profits. We will be considering responses over the coming months.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman",,"2019-10-23T17:57:30.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149256/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149256/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149256/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 16 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what progress her Department has made on extending the support offered to public sector teams aspiring to form mutuals to other social sector organisations that wish to deliver public services.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149257","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>As outlined in the Civil Society Strategy, this government is committed to enabling the generation of social value through a range of measures.</p><p> </p><p>The Strategy is forward-looking and long-term. Our immediate priority is to expand use of the Social Value Act in central government. Through a joint DCMS and Cabinet Office programme, all major procurements by government departments will explicitly evaluate social value as appropriate, rather than just ‘consider’ it as currently, providing it does not add complexity or cost to the procurement process, restrict markets or exclude small businesses from government contracts.</p><p> </p><p>Use of the Act will be extended to goods and works contracts, in addition to those for services and 4000 commercial buyers will be trained on how to take account of social value and procure successfully from a diverse range of organisations.</p><p> </p><p>While the programme focuses on central government, the changes will have more of an impact due to the number of supplier markets we have in common with the wider public sector as well as the private sector.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman","674 ; 675 ; 676 ; 677","2019-10-23T17:58:13.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149257/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149257/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149257/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 16 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken towards broadening the range of funding options for community initiatives.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149258","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-23","<p>As outlined in the Civil Society Strategy, this government is committed to enabling the generation of social value through a range of measures.</p><p> </p><p>The Strategy is forward-looking and long-term. Our immediate priority is to expand use of the Social Value Act in central government. Through a joint DCMS and Cabinet Office programme, all major procurements by government departments will explicitly evaluate social value as appropriate, rather than just ‘consider’ it as currently, providing it does not add complexity or cost to the procurement process, restrict markets or exclude small businesses from government contracts.</p><p> </p><p>Use of the Act will be extended to goods and works contracts, in addition to those for services and 4000 commercial buyers will be trained on how to take account of social value and procure successfully from a diverse range of organisations.</p><p> </p><p>While the programme focuses on central government, the changes will have more of an impact due to the number of supplier markets we have in common with the wider public sector as well as the private sector.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Matt Warman","673 ; 675 ; 676 ; 677","2019-10-23T17:58:13.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149258/answer","Biography information for Matt Warman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149258/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149258/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to page 17 of the Government’s Civil Society Strategy, what steps her Department has taken towards improving the use of the Public Services (Social Value) Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","674"
