rces/1149303/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149303/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","Developing Countries: Teenage Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment he has made of the effect of UK overseas development assistance on reducing adolescent birth rates in the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149304","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-22","<p>The UK is a leader in global education. Between 2000 and 2018, the global number of children out of primary school dropped from 100 million to 59 million. The biggest proportion of bilateral UK Aid education spend (35%) is for basic education and between 2015 and 2019 UK Aid supported 14.3 million children to gain a decent education, including at least 5.8 million girls.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson",,"2019-10-22T15:48:40.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149304/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149304/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149304/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","Developing Countries: Primary Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what effect UK overseas development assistance has had on the take up of primary education over the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149305","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-21","<p>All Access for All projects are due to be complete by 31 March 2024 at the latest. Retford is making good progress. The option selection process is finished and Network Rail will shortly start design works. Once that is complete we will have confirmed start and completion dates with construction scheduled to ensure minimal disruption to passengers.</p><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-10-21T16:04:19.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149305/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149305/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149305/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-15","Retford Station: Lifts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects work to be commenced on the lower level platform lift at Retford station.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149306","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-10-21","<p>Last month we announced that we will be consulting on whether to further restrict the import and export of hunting trophies.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation will cover a range of options. This is an important next step to determine how best to respond to conservation, welfare and ethical concerns. Following the consultation we will publish a Government response setting out any future policy actions required to move ahead on this important issue. The exact scope and timing of any further action will be subject to results of the consultation.</p>","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","571 ; 572 ; 574 ; 577","2019-10-21T15:21:10.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149306/answer","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149306/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149306/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-10-15","Animal Products: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, which animals will be covered by the ban on trophy hunting imports to the UK.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Mrs Pauline Latham","570"
