"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149348","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-10-21","<p>This measure ensures that there is no gap in entitlement for people who rely on means-tested benefits, such as Pension Credit. It provides a smooth transition between working-age and pension-age income related welfare support.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2019-10-21T14:46:44.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149348/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149348/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149348/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-10-15","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reason universal credit is paid pro-rata when a claimant becomes eligible part way through an assessment period for state pension credit  but not when a claimant becomes eligible for the state pension without state pension credit.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","481"
