"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149434","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-10-22","<p>​The Joint Statement on Explosive Weapons in Populated Areas presented at last year's UN General Assembly First Committee was a standalone document specific to the 2018 First Committee; it cannot be supported retrospectively.</p><p>​</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-10-22T16:08:56.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149434/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149434/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149434/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-10-15","Armed Conflict: Civilians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to UN General Assembly's First Committee on International Disarmament and International Security 2018 joint statement on the impact of explosive weapons in populated areas, whether the UK will become a signatory to that statement before the end of 2019.","false","Biography information for Fabian Hamilton","Leeds North East","Fabian Hamilton","439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149435","Treasury","false","2019-10-21","<p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) made a commitment to consult on the potential prohibition of the sale to retail consumers of derivatives referencing certain types of cryptoassets in the final report of the Cryptoasset Taskforce, comprised of HM Treasury, the Bank of England and the Financial Conduct Authority, in October 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The final decision on this consultation is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is operationally independent from government.</p><p> </p><p>The government continues to endorse the approach set out in that the Cryptoasset Taskforce report as the right way to facilitate innovation while protecting consumers and firms.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","491 ; 494","2019-10-21T15:19:06.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149435/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149435/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149435/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-15","Cryptocurrencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the Financial Conduct Authority’s compliance with (a) section 138I of the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 and (b) the powers under Article 42 of the Markets in Financial Instruments Regulation in relation to the proposed ban on the sale to retail clients of investment products that reference cryptoassets.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149436","Treasury","false","2019-10-21","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is independent of government. The question has been passed to the FCA.</p><p>The FCA will reply directly to Philip Davies MP by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","488 ; 490 ; 496 ; 497 ; 498 ; 948","2019-10-21T15:14:19.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149436/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149436/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149436/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-15","Cryptocurrencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Financial Conduct Authority's (FCA) consultation CP19/22: Restricting the sale to retail clients of investment products that reference cryptoassets, what the evidential basis was for the statement that the FCA had seen poor outcomes from the limited products currently available on EU trading venues in relation to Exchange Traded Notes that reference cryptoassets.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149437","Treasury","false","2019-10-21","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is independent of government. The question has been passed to the FCA.</p><p>The FCA will reply directly to Philip Davies MP by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-10-21T15:03:30.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149437/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149437/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149437/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-15","Cryptocurrencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of consultation responses to the Financial Conduct Authority's consultation entitled, CP19/22: Restricting the sale to retail clients of investment products that reference cryptoassets that opposed the proposals to ban the sale of cryptoasset investment products.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149438","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-10-21","<p>We intend to bring forward a comprehensive package for consumers as soon as possible. This will ensure consumers continue to enjoy competitive prices, quality products and services and that vulnerable consumers are treated fairly.</p><p>There is statutory protection for online ticket purchases and enforcement action is being taken where necessary.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2019-10-21T15:48:05.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149438/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149438/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149438/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-10-15","Tickets: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when the Consumer White Paper will be published, and whether that paper will include improved protections for online ticket purchases.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149439","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-10-21","<p>As the Chancellor announced at the Spending Round on 4 September, the Scottish Government will receive £160 million to support farmers and land managers. This funding will be provided over two years, with £80 million in 2019-20 and £80 million in 2020-21. The additional funding will be provided through the normal estimates process and it will be ring-fenced to ensure that it reaches farmers and land managers in Scotland.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2019-10-21T15:39:31.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149439/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149439/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-10-15","Agriculture: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to the Prime Minister's oral contribution of 25 July 2019, Official Report, column 1497, what the timescale is for the allocation of £160 million funding for farming to the Scottish Government .","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149440","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-22","<p>In January, the Government will host the UK-Africa Investment Summit. The summit will bring together African governments; UK and African businesses; and major international organisations. Formal invitations will be issued shortly from the Prime Minister to invited Heads of State.</p><p> </p><p>The cost of the event is in line with events of a similar size and ambition recently delivered by HMG. We will ensure it delivers value for money and provides positive benefits for both African countries and for the UK.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","717 ; 720 ; 721","2019-10-22T15:50:14.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149440/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149440/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","UK-Africa Investment Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether President Mnangagwa of Zimbabwe has been invited to the UK-Africa Investment Summit scheduled to take place in January 2020.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149441","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-21","<p>We would encourage people to practice safe sex by using condoms and to access their free, local sexual health services if they consider themselves to be at risk of infection. Local authorities have been mandated to commission comprehensive open access sexual health services and are best placed to understand and meet the public health needs of their local communities.</p><p>Data published by Public Health England show that more people are accessing sexual health services, with attendances increasing by 7% between 2017 and 2018. This continues the trend of increases in attendances seen over the past five years. To help manage the overall increase in demand, online services are increasingly being commissioning to manage lower risk and asymptomatic patients. These services also have the potential to reach groups not currently engaged with clinic services.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-10-21T16:53:30.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149441/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149441/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-15","Sexually Transmitted Infections: Haringey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to reduce rates of sexually transmitted infections in Haringey.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149442","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-22","<p>In January, the Government will host the UK-Africa Investment Summit. The summit will bring together African governments; UK and African businesses; and major international organisations. Formal invitations will be issued shortly from the Prime Minister to invited Heads of State.</p><p> </p><p>The cost of the event is in line with events of a similar size and ambition recently delivered by HMG. We will ensure it delivers value for money and provides positive benefits for both African countries and for the UK.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","715 ; 720 ; 721","2019-10-22T15:50:14.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149442/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149442/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","UK-Africa Investment Summit: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate he has made of the cost of the UK-Africa Investment Summit scheduled for January 2020.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149443","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-21","<p>The development of a national sexual health strategy is a key recommendation in the Health and Social Care Select Committee’s report on sexual health, which was published on 2 June 2019. The Government is currently considering the report’s recommendations and will publish a formal response shortly. In the Green Paper consultation ‘Advancing Our Health – Prevention in the 2020s’, we sought views on priorities for a possible new strategy and will consider the responses carefully.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-10-21T16:59:16.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149443/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149443/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149443/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-15","Sexually Transmitted Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether the Government plans to review its sexual health policy to reduce rates of sexually transmitted infections.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149444","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-22","<p>The UK remains a world leader in efforts to end new HIV infections and preventable AIDS-related deaths including through our major investment in the Global Fund which in 2018 helped protect over 700,000 babies from being infected by their mothers. We are now stepping up on efforts to end preventable deaths of mothers, new-born babies and children in the developing world by 2030.</p><p>We work closely with many international partners including the African Union on UK priorities including HIV. For example, through our seat on the Executive Board of Unitaid, we discuss ways to tackle child deaths from AIDS, with a representative of African countries designated by the African Union.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-10-22T15:51:23.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149444/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149444/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149444/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","Sub-Saharan Africa: AIDS","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions his Department has had representatives of African Union on tackling child deaths from Aids in sub-Saharan Southern Africa.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149445","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-22","<p>In January, the Government will host the UK-Africa Investment Summit. The summit will bring together African governments; UK and African businesses; and major international organisations. Formal invitations will be issued shortly from the Prime Minister to invited Heads of State.</p><p> </p><p>The cost of the event is in line with events of a similar size and ambition recently delivered by HMG. We will ensure it delivers value for money and provides positive benefits for both African countries and for the UK.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","715 ; 717 ; 721","2019-10-22T15:50:14.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149445/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149445/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","UK-Africa Investment Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether President Biya of Cameroon has been invited to the UK-Africa Investment Summit scheduled for January 2020.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149446","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-22","<p>In January, the Government will host the UK-Africa Investment Summit. The summit will bring together African governments; UK and African businesses; and major international organisations. Formal invitations will be issued shortly from the Prime Minister to invited Heads of State.</p><p> </p><p>The cost of the event is in line with events of a similar size and ambition recently delivered by HMG. We will ensure it delivers value for money and provides positive benefits for both African countries and for the UK.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","715 ; 717 ; 720","2019-10-22T15:50:14.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149446/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149446/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-10-15","UK-Africa Investment Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether President Teodoro Obiang Nguema Mbasogo of Equatorial Guinea has been invited to the UK-Africa Investment Summit scheduled for January 2020.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149447","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-10-22","<p>We submitted our full response to the Select Committee on October 1st 2019. This was published on October 10th 2019.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Helen Whately",,"2019-10-22T11:27:42.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149447/answer","Biography information for Helen Whately","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149447/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149447/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-10-15","Gardens: Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to respond to the recommendations made by the Digital, Culture, Media and Sport Committee in its Fourteenth Report of Session 2017-19 entitled Garden design and tourism, HC 2002.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149448","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-10-23","<p>The Government has encouraged UK and EU regulators to sign mutual recognition agreements that provide routes for recognition for qualifications of UK and EU professionals in the event of leaving the EU without a deal. This will ensure UK professionals are able to practise in other parties’ jurisdictions.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-10-23T11:07:19.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149448/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149448/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149448/answer","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149448/answer/previousversion/704","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-10-15","Professions: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many mutual recognition agreements for professional qualifications (a) the UK has signed with EU member states and (b) plans to sign by 31 October 2019.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149449","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-10-21","<p>The Government continues to work closely with the fuel supply industry to ensure they have taken appropriate mitigating measures to prevent any disruption to their supplies and have plans in place to respond to a range of EU Exit scenarios, including in the event of Brexit without a Withdrawal Agreement. As part of that engagement, we have been in contact with all six UK refineries, who have reviewed their supply chains and confirmed that they have sufficient stockpiles of essential consumables.</p>","Spelthorne","Kwasi  Kwarteng",,"2019-10-21T11:56:46.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149449/answer","Biography information for Kwasi  Kwarteng","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149449/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149449/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-10-15","Refineries: Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps her Department has taken to safeguard the supply of reagents and additives for UK fuel refineries in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149450","Treasury","false","2019-10-21","<p>As set out in the Government’s No-Deal Readiness Report, the Government has implemented a range of temporary permissions and transitional regimes for various EEA inbound financial services firms. These regimes will in most cases last three years from exit day, allowing EEA businesses to continue operating as normal in the UK while they go through the process to obtain full UK authorisation or recognition.</p><p> </p><p>While the Government has established the framework for these regimes in legislation, which Parliament has approved, the UK’s financial services regulators have been tasked with administering the operation of these regimes. Further information can be found on the regulators’ websites: https://www.fca.org.uk/brexit and https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/eu-withdrawal.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-10-21T14:49:50.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149450/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149450/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149450/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-10-15","Financial Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 71 of the Government's No-Deal Readiness Report, what temporary measures will be introduced to create a standalone regime for financial services when the UK leaves the EU; and what estimate he has made of the length of time that each such measure will be in place.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149451","Home Office","false","2019-10-21","<p>The numbers of visa applications made, approved and refused under Seasonal Workers Pilot scheme are published in the quarterly Immigration statistics. This information is available on the Gov.uk website at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-year-ending-june-2019/list-of-tables" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-year-ending-june-2019/list-of-tables</a></p><p>The Seasonal Workers Pilot is a UK wide scheme. The recruitment and placement of migrant workers is managed by the two scheme operators who have been licensed to manage the pilot. Both scheme operators cover the whole of the country and in 2019 both operators were allocated 1,250 scheme places. The Home Office does not hold information relating to the allocation of workers to specific regions.</p><p>Any places allocated to applicants who subsequently decide not to travel to the UK are made available to other applicants.</p><p> </p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy","723 ; 724 ; 725 ; 726 ; 727 ; 728","2019-10-21T16:09:46.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149451/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149451/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1149451/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-10-15","Agriculture: Seasonal Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications to the seasonal workers pilot scheme were (a) successful and (b) unsuccessful.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","722"
